Residents of Kiserian, Ongata Rongai and Karen will today protest against rogue matatu drivers plying the route.The protests follow the accident on Sunday in which a matatu overturned on Lang&rsquo;ata Road killing four people and injuring six.Residents said they will walk from Tusky&rsquo;s in Rongai to the Lang&rsquo;ata cemetery. &ldquo;We are saying enough is enough. The reckless matatu culture and police complicity in the madness will not be accepted as lives are being lost,&rdquo; a resident said.